body:
This example performs the following actions:

- Specifies two `ClientBulkWriteModel` instances in an array. The
  first model specifies a delete many operation on the `movies`
  collection, and the second model specifies a delete one operation
  on the `users` collection.

- Calls the `bulkWrite()` method on a client and passes an array of models as
  a parameter.

- Prints the number of modified documents.

**Input:**

```javascript
const clientDeletes = [{
    namespace: "sample_mflix.movies",
    name: "deleteMany",
    filter: {
        rated: "R"
    }
}, {
    namespace: "sample_mflix.users",
    name: "deleteOne",
    filter: {
        email: "emilia_clarke@gameofthron.es"
    }
}];

const clientDeleteRes = await client.bulkWrite(clientDeletes);
console.log(`Deleted documents: ${clientDeleteRes.deletedCount}`);
```

**Output:**

```console
Deleted documents: 5538
```

